        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 5:15PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 515 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles east of Castleberry, or 10 miles south of Evergreen, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Evergreen, Castleberry, and I65 And US 84.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
